### Phase 2: CMS Ingestion Script


#### 2.1 Create ingestion script
- [ ] File: `ouiispeak-cms/scripts/ingest-lady-lesson.ts`
- [ ] Accept file path as CLI arg: `npx tsx scripts/ingest-lady-lesson.ts <path-to-lesson.json>`
- [ ] Use existing CMS infrastructure: `lib/data/lessons`, `lib/data/groups`, `lib/data/slides`


#### 2.2 Read & validate LaDy output
- [ ] Read JSON from path
- [ ] Validate against LaDy lesson shape (or minimal schema): `lessonId`, `targetNodeIds`, `activities[]`
- [ ] Exit with clear error if invalid


#### 2.3 Map and create Lesson
- [ ] Create lesson via `createLesson()` with:
 - `title`: derived from `lessonId` or first target (e.g. truncated)
 - `module_id`: map from config or use "Incoming" / placeholder module
 - `status`: `waiting_review`
 - `metadata`: `{ canonical_node_key: targetNodeIds, run_id: compilerMeta?.runId, lessonSku: lessonId }`


---


### Phase 3: Mapping Layer


#### 3.1 Create Lady-to-CMS mapper
- [ ] File: `ouiispeak-cms/lib/mappers/ladyToCmsMapper.ts`
- [ ] Map LaDy types → CMS types:
 - LaDy `EXPLAIN` → CMS Group + Slide (type `standard_text` or equivalent)
 - LaDy `PRACTICE` → CMS Group + Slide(s) (prompt + optional expectedAnswer)
- [ ] Resolve slide_type mapping: LaDy pedagogical types → CMS slide constants (`constants/slideConstants.ts`)


#### 3.2 Activity → Group mapping (no nested items)
- **Note:** LaDy Activities do NOT have `activity.items`. Each Activity = 1 Group.
- [ ] For each `activity` in `ladyLesson.activities`:
 - Create Group: `title` = activity.type, `order` = index
 - Create 1+ Slides from `content` (EXPLAIN) or `prompt` + `expectedAnswer` (PRACTICE)


#### 3.3 Slide props validation
- [ ] Use existing CMS slide props validation (Zod or similar)
- [ ] Ensure mapped props satisfy CMS schema


